-- U.S. Orange-Juice Sales Fell 11.2% in Four Weeks Ended Oct. 30, Data Show
-- B y   L e s l i e   P a t t o n
-- 2010-11-15T20:26:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-15/u-s-orange-juice-sales-fell-11-2-in-four-weeks-ended-oct-30-data-show.html
Orange-juice sales by U.S. retailers
fell 11.2 percent in the four weeks ended Oct. 30, compared with
a year earlier, the Florida Department of Citrus  said  today in
an e-mailed report. Retail prices rose 5.2 percent on average to
$5.68 a gallon from $5.40, the agency said, citing Nielsen Co.
data.  To contact the reporter on this story:
